snippet.textDisplay: Although it is apparently the least flamboyant in otherwise a shiny album, Soz O Salaam is vocally most textured, nuanced, evocative track. When the second generation brothers join in, it is *almost* akin to some vedic chants in temples. What control from Ustad Ghulam Mustafa Khan and the grandson! Brilliant. The kid literally hits it out of the park when he does what he does at 3:12. Heavenly,heavenly! All this before the master takes over and produces one of his finest pieces on the continuum.
snippet.textOriginal: Although it is apparently the least flamboyant in otherwise a shiny album, Soz O Salaam is vocally most textured, nuanced, evocative track.
